name: Komoka Provincial Park
review: Great place to take a hike and clear your head.  The trails are will maintained and clean.  The variety of terrain as well as the different trail skill levels make it so you want to hike more and more!

name: Komoka Provincial Park
review: We love hiking here. Parking is now paid, which is $5.25 for 2 hours, as a minimum, however, the trails are great, and scenic. Great place for a family walk or a date, and just minutes from the city

review:

name: Komoka Provincial Park
review:
Even on a cold fall day this provincial park is magical. Set along the Thames River, there are beautiful look outs, wildlife, and a multitude of paths. 

Only downside.. there is a fee for admission.

name: Komoka Provincial Park
review: Saw Two Bald Eagles circling an hour ago it was fantastic.

name: Komoka Provincial Park
review: Excellent park with lots of parking. Long calm relaxing scenic walks in your choice of 3 directs. Lots of animals & birds. Takes you right to the Thames river. There's a nice lookout spot in the winter & spring/fall without leaves that lets you see the horizon from a good height. I‚Äôve come here 7 times this year.

name: Komoka Provincial Park
review: Great hiking spot would give 5 stars if it wasn't for the expensive parking $5.25 for 2 hours.

name: Komoka Provincial Park
review: Great place for a hike just a short drive outside of London Ontario. Parking is paid now, there is a public washroom. Trails are nice along the river. A good mix of hills and valleys, trails in the woods and also through the meadow valleys. Horses allowed on a few trails. Always have a good time here.

name: Komoka Provincial Park
review: I thoroughly enjoyed a mid day walk under the canopy of the Komoka treed park. The ground was easy to navigate. There were some slight inclines that required a little extra effort. I used my urban poles which helped with any climbing. This is new and the only upgrade is a public toilet and gravel for the parking area.

name: Komoka Provincial Park
review: Beautiful park for walking and hiking. Parking is I think $10, which seems a bit high.

name: Komoka Provincial Park
review:

The only ...

review: Good for a quick hike. The new parking lot although well maintained is overpriced.

name: Komoka Provincial Park
review: Good but the parking meter didn't work

name: Komoka Provincial Park

name: Komoka Provincial Park

name: Komoka Provincial Park
review: Nice park for hiking.  Annoying how there is a charge for parking now though.  And that they closed the entrance across the park.  2 access points was much more convenient.

name: Komoka Provincial Park
